# Telco CRM — REST API Standards

## URL Structure

- Always prefix all REST endpoints with `/api/v1/`.
- Use URI-based versioning only. Never use header-based or query-param versioning.
- Resource names must be **plural nouns**: `/customers`, `/orders`, `/subscriptions`, `/invoices`.
- Sub-resources follow the parent: `/customers/{id}/addresses`, `/tickets/{id}/comments`.

```java
// ✅ GOOD
@RequestMapping("/api/v1/customers")

// ❌ BAD
@RequestMapping("/api/customer")
@RequestMapping("/v1/api/customer")
```

## HTTP Method Semantics

| Method | Use for |
|---|---|
| `GET` | Read-only retrieval; must have no side effects |
| `POST` | Create a resource or trigger a command |
| `PUT` | Full replacement of a resource |
| `PATCH` | Partial update of a resource |
| `DELETE` | Soft delete only (set `deletedAt`; never physical removal for customer data) |

## Error Format — RFC 7807 Problem Details

All error responses must conform to RFC 7807. Never return plain strings or custom error envelopes.

```json
{
  "type": "https://telco.example/errors/customer-not-found",
  "title": "Customer not found",
  "status": 404,
  "detail": "Customer with id 1234 does not exist",
  "instance": "/api/v1/customers/1234",
  "correlationId": "9f3c1b..."
}
```

## Pagination

Always use Spring Data `Pageable` for list endpoints. Never return unbounded lists.

```java
// ✅ GOOD
@GetMapping
public Page<CustomerResponse> list(Pageable pageable) { ... }
// Default: ?page=0&size=20&sort=createdAt,desc
```

## Required Headers

| Header | Direction | Applies to |
|---|---|---|
| `Idempotency-Key` | Request (client → service) | All POST endpoints in `payment-service` and `order-service` |
| `Correlation-Id` | Injected by gateway | All services; must be propagated to all log entries |
| `X-User-Id` | Injected by gateway | All authenticated requests |
| `X-User-Roles` | Injected by gateway | All authenticated requests |

```java
// ✅ Always read identity from gateway-injected headers
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public ResponseEntity<OrderResponse> get(
    @PathVariable UUID id,
    @RequestHeader("X-User-Id") String userId) { ... }
```

## Data Type Conventions

- **Dates**: Always use ISO-8601 UTC (`OffsetDateTime` or `Instant`). Never use `java.util.Date` or epoch longs in DTOs.
- **Money**: Use `BigDecimal` for amounts. Always include a separate `currency` field with value `"TRY"`. Never use `double` or `float` for monetary values.
- **IDs**: Use `UUID` as the primary key type on all entities and DTOs.

```java
// ✅ GOOD
private BigDecimal amount;
private String currency = "TRY";
private OffsetDateTime createdAt;

// ❌ BAD
private double amount;
private long createdAt;
```

## Performance Target

- p95 API response time must be below **300 ms**.
- Wrap all outbound OpenFeign calls with Resilience4j circuit breaker and retry.
- Cache product catalog reads in Redis to avoid repeated synchronous calls during order creation.
